<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Seeks More Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- The municipal government of
Shanghai, China's industrial and financial center, today announced
plans to seek investments for 168 key industrial projects.
</P>
<P>
The projects, which will require total investments of over 4.1
billion U.S. dollars, are part of the city's efforts to implement
the central government's decision to increase domestic demand,
increase employment and achieve that growth target for gross
domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
The projects cover wide-ranging sectors, including automobile
parts, electronics, telecommunications facilities, modern
medicines and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The projects are primarily designed for the Pudong New Area
which over the past eight years of development has emerged as
Shanghai's new base for economic growth, and for adjusting the
industrial structure.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai's gross industrial output value is expected to rise at
an annual rate of between 12-13 percent over the next three years,
with the figure expected to hit 700 billion yuan by the year
2,000, according to Huang Qifan, director of the Municipal Economic
Commission.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
