<HEADLINE> St. Lucia to Strengthen Ties With China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 2 (Xinhua) -- China and St. Lucia have
enjoyed sound exchanges and cooperation in all areas since the two
nations forged diplomatic ties in 1997 and friendly cooperative
relations will be strengthened even further in the future.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister Mario Michel, who also serves as first
deputy leader of the St. Lucian Labor Party (SLP), made the
remarks today during an exclusive interview with the Xinhua News
Agency.
</P>
<P>
Michel said his visit to China coincides with the first
anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic ties between the
two nations. He pointed to the visit as "successful, fruitful,
rewarding and very interesting."
</P>
<P>
The St. Lucian leader said he has visited numerous places in
Beijing and Tianjin, including historical sites and modern
facilities. He has also met with Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
and various high-ranking officials from the Foreign Ministry and
Ministry of Education.
</P>
<P>
Michel cited his "favorable" impressions and noted that he has
acquired a deeper undersanding of the Chinese economy, political
situation, history and culture.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
