<HEADLINE> St. Lucia to Strengthen Ties With China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said, "Forging diplomatic relations with the People's
Republic of China represents a major decision made by the new
government of St. Lucia once the SLP emerged as the ruling party."
</P>
<P>
St. Lucia-China relations have developed smoothly, said Michel
adding that the economic and technological cooperation agreement
signed by the two countries calls for China to participate in the
design and construction of a free trade economic zone and his
nation's first sports stadium.
</P>
<P>
China's economic and technological assistance to St. Lucia over
the past year fully demonstrates St. Lucia's correct decision
in forging diplomatic ties with China, said Michel.
</P>
<P>
He said one goal of his visit is to establish and develop
friendly links between the SLP and the Communist Party of China
(CPC), and he noted the visit has provided an opportunity for
formal contacts and laid a solid foundation for the development of
party-to-party relations.
</P>
<P>
Michel cited the CPC as a "strong and resilient" party with a
history of over 70 years. China has witnessed sustained and stable
economic development under the leadership of the CPC, according to
Michel.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the SLP will draw lessons and learn from the CPC,
and expressed hope that the two parties will expand exchanges and
cooperations in various areas. 
