<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Germany, Cote d'Ivoire Sign Debt Rescheduling Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Germany and the Republic of Cote
d'Ivoire have signed eight debt rescheduling agreements including
a debt relief of 53 million marks (about 30 million U.S. dollars)
for the African country, the German Finance Ministry announced
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreements, the repayments of another 100 million
marks (about 57 million dollars) of debts owed by Cote d'Ivoire to
Germany have been rescheduled over the next 40 years, the Finance
Ministry said in a statement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
