while
Anwar along with Bank Negara (State Bank), whose governor and
deputy
governor resigned four days ago, had adhered to International
Monetary
Fund style policies particularly in maintaining tight monetary
policies
including high interest rates.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's economy slipped into recession with gross domestic
product
declining 2.8 percent and 6.8 percent in the first two quarters of
the
year respectively.
