<HEADLINE> UK to Give Russia Longer Missile Firing Notice Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- British Defense Secretary
George Robertson said Wednesday Britain was planning to give
Russia five days notice of any test firing of its Trident nuclear
missiles compared with 24 hours previously.
</P>
<P>
Robertson was quoted by Reuters as saying that this action was
in line with a military accord reached earlier Wednesday in Moscow
by U.S. and Russian leaders.
</P>
<P>
Under the Russo-American agreement, Moscow and Washington
pledged to alert each other to any worldwide missile launches in
the future.
</P>
<P>
"We strongly support the initiatives announced today by the
United States and Russia," Robertson said.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that Britain was looking forward to participating
in any discussions on a multilateral ballistic missile launch
notification regime, calling it "a means of increasing stability
worldwide." 
</P>
