<HEADLINE> UNITA Members in Angolan Govt Call for Removal of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Members of the opposition
National Union for Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) who hold
posts in the Angolan government Wednesday called for dismissing
Jonas Savimbi from the UNITA presidency.
</P>
<P>
In a declaration issued here, these officials including some
suspended ministers and deputy ministers urged all the patriotic
UNITA members to keep onto the track of the Angolan peace process
and choose the route of national reconciliation and democracy.
</P>
<P>
Jorge Valenti, who was suspended Monday as minister of hotel
and tourism, read the declaration at a press conference with
Deputy Defense Minister Demostenes Chilingutila and former UNITA
general secretary Eugenio Manuvakola in presence.
</P>
<P>
The declaration said that the patriotic members of the UNITA
have chosen the route of peace, national reconciliation and
democracy instead of civil war in their political struggle.
</P>
<P>
They hope that the hard-won cease-fire will be cherished and
the final tasks written in the 1994 Lusaka Peace Accords will be
completed with the help of the United Nations observer mission,
it said.
</P>
<P>
For this purpose, it called for removing Savimbi from the
presidency of the UNITA, dismissing the current leaders, setting
up a provisional leadership and holding a national congress.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan peace process is facing the serious crisis in four
years. The UNITA did not disband all of its troops and refused
to turn the areas formerly controlled by the rebel group into the
hands of the government.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the renewed fightings between the rebel soldiers and
the government troops have resulted in hundreds of deaths and
displaced many people.
</P>
<P>
On August 24, the UNITA announced a decision to stop its
cooperation with the U.N. observers from Russia, the United
States and Portugal.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government Monday suspended the UNITA members in
the government of national unity and the congress of people.
</P>
<P>
Prior to this, the UNITA held 70 seats in the parliament and
had four ministers and seven deputy ministers in the government.
</P>
</TEXT>
