<HEADLINE> U.S. First Lady Praises N.Irish Women's Peace Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 2 (Xinhua) -- U.S. First Lady Hillary Clinton
said in Belfast Wednesday that America would support the Northern
Irish people in their quest for peace.
</P>
<P>
Hillary arrived at the Northern Irish capital Wednesday
afternoon to attend a conference on women's development. Her
husband President Bill Clinton will arrive in the British province
Thursday for a one-day visit,
</P>
<P>
At the conference, she praised women across the divided
community for striving to bury animosity and heal the wounds of a
conflict pitting pro-Irish and pro-British militias that claimed
3,600 lives in the course of three decades.
</P>
<P>
