<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, September 2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN -- The World Bank (WB) has proposed Jordan adjust
investment structure and speed up privatization to revive its
national economy, said a Jordan Businessmen Association (JBA)
statement obtained here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The suggestion was made by John Page, WB's chief economist for
the Middle East and North Africa Region, during a JBA-sponsored
meeting on Tuesday in Amman.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian government has to adjust the current investment
structure by directing investors' priorities towards the
productive sector rather than building houses in order to create
"a balance between commercial and non-commercial investments,"
said Page.
</P>
<P>
A balanced investment structure, plus a healthy ratio of
investment to the gross domestic products (GDP), will contribute
much to reviving Jordan's economy, whose growth rates almost
grounded to zero in the past few years, said Page.
(BC-Jordan-Economy-World Bank)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran announced on Wednesday to put eight German
companies on trial for exporting chemical weapons to Iraq during
the 1980-88 Iran-Iraq war.
</P>
<P>
Director general of Iran's judiciary public relations office
Fotovat Nassiri Savadkouhi said that the German companies would
go on trial in Tehran public court, the official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
Savadkouhi stated the chemical weapons provided to Iraq by the
German companies caused 10,000 deaths and 50,000 injuries in Iran.
(BC-Iran-German-Iraq)
</P>
