submitted by the United States and Britain to the Security Council
proposing the council's review of sanctions on Iraq every 60 days
be suspended.
</P>
<P>
"Suspending the review of sanctions, so far held for 40 times
with no result achieved, means nothing to Iraq other than
confirming the fact that continued dealing with UNSCOM is of no
use," Aziz said.
</P>
<P>
Aziz said that the adoption of the draft resolution by the
Security Council would implicate that the council attaches no
seriousness to Iraq's legitimate demands, which he said should not
be ignored. (BC-Iraq-UN-Draft Resolution)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey on Wednesday urged Cyprus and Greece to
reconsider the proposal put forward by Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf
Denktash for creating a confederation in the divided Mediterranean
island.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a weekly press conference here, Turkish Foreign
Ministry spokesman Necati Utkan said that if the proposal was
wasted, the tension in Cyprus might escalate to a level which
would lead to a permanent division of the island.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Denktash proposed that a bi-communal confederation
"equal states " of Turkish and Greek Cypriots be established to
settle the long-running Cyprus crisis.
</P>
<P>
But Cyprus and its closest ally Greece have categorically
rejected Denktash's proposal. (BC-Turkey-Cyprus-Proposal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- U.S. President Bill Clinton pledged on Wednesday
to make efforts to advance the Israeli-Palestinian peace talks
which have been stalled for 18 months, Israeli Prime Minister's
Office said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
