<HEADLINE> Syria, Iraq Working to Restore Diplomatic Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Syria and Iraq are working
toward the restoration of diplomatic ties, Syrian diplomatic
sources said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said Syria reopened its trade center in Baghdad
Thursday and an Iraqi trade center is expected to open soon in
Damascus. The moves were widely seen as the lastest sign of
growing ties between the two neighbors after a lapse of 17 years.
</P>
<P>
Syria's Trade Minister Mohammed Mehdi Saleh is now in Baghdad
to prepare for an exhibition of Syrian products, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Iraq cut diplomatic relations with Syria in 1981 because of its
support for Iran in the 1980-1988 Iran-Iraq war.
</P>
<P>
A thaw in the relations began after Syria sent a trade
delegation to Iraq in May 1997 and visits at ministerial level
have been exchanged.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the two countries has been picking up in the past
two years, during which Syria has exported 250 million
U.S. dollars worth of medicine, clothing and food to Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's reopening of the Syrian trade center followed the
August 20 agreement between the two countries to re-start a
pipeline that carries Iraqi crude oil to Syrian Meiterranean ports.
</P>
<P>
The sources noted that officials from Syrian Foreign Ministry
will arrive in Baghdad within days to inspect the premises of the
Syrian embassy which was closed down 17 years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980903.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Snubs Duma Suggestion to Give Up Premiership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Russian Acting Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin on Thursday rejected a call from the State
Duma for him to voluntarily give up his nomination as premier.
</P>
<P>
"I shall not take such an irresponsible decision either in the
interest of work or calls of my conscience," Chernomyrdin said at
a government meeting.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma, or the lower house of parliament, on Monday
overwhelmingly rejected Chernomyrdin's nomination and passed a
resolution Wednesday urging him to reject the post.
</P>
<P>
"I have no other country or destiny. My children and
grandchildren will live here," the Itar-Tass news agency quoted
Chernomyrdin as saying.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the call for a speedy establishment of a
"government of concord" grouping professionals and those willing
to work, rather than those with political ambitions.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin also refuted accusations that he was using the
premiership as a springboard to presidency.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Chernomyrdin continued his efforts
Thursday to muster support, meeting leaders of 33 administrative
regions.
</P>
<P>
He admitted that addressing the situation with "usual
approaches" is "almost impossible."
</P>
<P>
There are reports that Chernomyrdin will make "sensational"
announcements Friday in the Federation Council, or upper house of
parliament.
</P>
<P>
"Russia again has been plunged into a serious spiral of the
crisis which negatively affects the whole economy, and in these
conditions the government needs to decide what to do and how so as
not to allow serious shocks," he said, noting that "this is the
main thing one needs to avoid."
</P>
<P>
The State Duma is scheduled to hold a second round of voting
on Chernomyrdin's nomination Friday. Most opposition parties have
indicated that they would vote against him.
</P>
<P>
Under Russian constitution, if the Duma blocks the nomination
of the premiership three times, the president will have to either
name a new candidate or dissolve the lower chamber.
</P>
<P>
However, a Wednesday letter to Chernomyrdin says that "the
dissolution of the State Duma will not alleviate the
crisis. Rather, it will bring about irreconcilable political
confrontation."
</P>
<P>
"Chernomyrdin has found himself in the center of a conflict and
now has to make a decision which will shape the fate of the entire
country as well as his own," the document said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
