<HEADLINE> Thailand to Spend 2.3 Billion Baht for Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Transport and
Communications Ministry of Thailand is spending some 2.3 billion
baht (57.5 million U.S. dollars) on supporting the December 6-20
Asian Games, local reports said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At sports venues, the ministry will install 23,000 telephones,
3,580 public phones, and Internet outlet, the Bangkok Post quoted
minister Suthep Thueksuban as saying.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will also complete an extended section of the Din
Daeng-Don Muang tollway, Bangkok's eastern ring road, U-turn
flyovers on the highway leading to one of the main sports
complexes, and new small roads along Bangkok's railway tracks.
</P>
<P>
These routes will serve traffic heading for sports venues, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Preparation for the Games will include 1,850 buses, 302
limousines, 300 vans, and 40 trucks as shuttle service for
athletes, officials, and spectators.
</P>
<P>
The ministry, through its Communications Authority of
Thailand, will issue eight million special postage stamps to mark
the Games.
</P>
<P>
Thai Airway International, a state enterprise under the
ministry's jurisdiction, will also help by offering
round-the-clock catering service consisting of 260 different
international dishes.
</P>
<P>
The national airline will also show Games advertisements on
flights and place ads in leading papers in tickets for the Games
through outlets in Thailand and Games member countries, and
invite 2,500 international journalists to cover the event.
</P>
</TEXT>
