<HEADLINE> Sweden Puts Stake in 2004 Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Sweden has decided to
invest big cashes to improve its sports image by training
athletes for the 2004 Olympic Games, the Swedish News Agency said
here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 280 million kronas (some 35 million US dollars) was
to be financed by the Swedish government, the commercial circles
and the Swedish Olympic Committee as funds to train its athletes
for the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Sweden hopes to cash in the funds for at least 20 medals in
the 2004 summer games.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be distributed by the Swedish Olympic Committee
with an annual expenditure of 5 million US dollars to train its
best athletes and medal hopefuls. 
