<HEADLINE> American City to Attract Chinese Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The American city of Vernon
in the State of California hosted an investment fair today in
Shanghai, China's largest commercial center.
</P>
<P>
Vernon, located in the suburbs of Los Angeles, is home to 1,200
enterprises, including 150 Asian-funded ventures, in the clothing,
automobile and food processing sectors.
</P>
<P>
Larry Gonzales, an official with Vernon Redevelopment Agency,
said that Shanghai is China's major economic center and noted that
a number of large enterprises in the vast metropolis have the
wherewithal to enter international economic arena.
</P>
<P>
Farzam Kamalabadi, president of Future Trends International
Group Corporation, said that businessmen worldwide are keenly
aware of China's steady and rapid economic development over the
past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
"Economic and trade cooperation and exchanges between China and
the United States will undoubtedly enter into a more prosperous
era," according to Kamalabadi.
</P>
<P>
Companies from the United States initiated 2,300 projects in
Shanghai between January-June this year, with total investments
approaching 3.3 billion US dollars. In addition, Shanghai
companies established more than 20 Chinese enterprises in the
United States during the period. 
</P>
