<HEADLINE> Ministry Urges Prompt Reconstruction in Flood-Stricken Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Civil Affairs
has urged local departments to waste no time in building new homes
for flood victims and ensure that at least a third of houses are
rebuilt before the arrival of winter.
</P>
<P>
Donated funds and materials, with the exception of funds for
specified purposes, and central government allocations should be
mainly used to build houses, and local governments should finalize
reconstruction plans without delay, according to a senior ministry
official.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that heavy flooding in the Yangtze
River Valley and along the Nenjiang and Songhua rivers in
northeastern China have destroyed a total of 4.97 million houses
and affected well over 230 million people.
</P>
<P>
The official said winter usually arrives early in northeastern
China, and stressed that local governments in Heilongjiang and
Jilin provinces, as well as the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region
should accelerate reconstruction efforts.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has distributed over 30,000 tents to victims in
disaster areas and is working diligently to provide all possible
assistance to displaced people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
