<HEADLINE> Macao IDD Callers to Britain, Taiwan to Have Cheap Sundays </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- IDD users calling from Macao to
Britain and China's Taiwan area will see lower toll as the Macao
Telecommunications Company (CTM) will launch an IDD discount
program on every Sunday (i.e. 6, 13, 20, and 27) of September.
</P>
<P>
A news release issued by CTM on Thursday announced that all
fixed telephone and mobile phone customers can enjoy the program
with no need of registration in advance.
</P>
<P>
On these Sundays, all IDD calls to the United Kingdom of
Britain and the Taiwan region will be charged at 5.99 patacas
(0.75 U.S. dollars) per minute and 4.99 patacas per minute,
respectively, about two-thirds of the normal prices.
</P>
<P>
The program will be available 24 hours in the four
days. However, it will not apply to International FreeCalls,
Operator Assisted Calls, public and private pay phones, EasyCall
Card, SmartCard, ISDN and mobile phones on roaming. 
</P>
</TEXT>
