<DOCNO> XIE19980903.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Views on Selection Committee Solicited in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- From September 3 to 6, social
bodies and people of various sectors in Macao will have a good
chance to express their opinions on the region's future.
</P>
<P>
The administrative working group of the Preparatory Committee
for the Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) is conducting a
four-day consultation on the Selection Committee which will
produce the first government of the future Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13 consultation meetings will be held in the four
days, sources at the Secretariat of the Preparatory Committee said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to rules enacted by the National People's Congress
(NPC), China's highest organ of state power, the Selection
Committee should consist of only permanent Macao residents and
have the broadest representation of people from all walks of life.
</P>
<P>
The rules stipulate that the Selection Committee will be
composed of 200 members, including 60 from industrial, commercial
and financial sectors, 50 from cultural, educational and
professional sectors, 50 from sectors of labor, social service and
religion and 40 representatives chosen from Portuguese Macao
government employees, Macao deputies to the NPC and Macao members
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
By means of consultation and nomination after consultation, the
Selection Committee will produce the candidate for the chief
executive of the Macao SAR government and submit the candidacy to
the central government for appointment.
</P>
<P>
Chen Ziying, secretary-general of the Preparatory Committee and
vice-director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office under the
State Council, said before the consultation meeting on Thursday
that the Preparatory Committee will formulate a detailed method
for forming the Selection Committee.
</P>
<P>
"The Preparatory Committee expects to hear opinions from the
most inclusive social bodies and personages of various sectors in
Macao," Chen said.
</P>
<P>
In addition to such consultation meetings, social bodies and
individuals in Macao can also submit written materials to the
Secretariat of the Preparatory Committee, talk with Preparatory
Committee members or express their views via the local media, he
said.
</P>
<P>
"The administrative working group will surely have
conscientious discussions on such opinions and decide the method
on the formation of the Selection Committee through democratic
procedures," Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past several days, a number of social bodies have
stated their views on forming Selection Committee, or submitted
written opinions to the Secretariat of the Preparatory Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
