<HEADLINE> All-China Women's Federation Elects New Executive Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The All-China Women's
Federation (ACWF) elected its eighth executive committee today.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,300 ACWF delegates selected 219 women, including
Peng Peiyun and Gu Xiulian, during the election held in the second
plenary meeting of the Eighth National Congress of Chinese Women
held today in the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
An additional 20 members were added and members of the new
executive committee reportedly have more extensive educational
backgrounds. This year's committee is also considered to be more
representative.
</P>
<P>
Almost 96 percent of the members have completed at least two
years of higher education, up 10 higher on the figure for the
previous committee, according to one official.
</P>
<P>
The ACWF president and vice presidents will be elected on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The ACWF, founded in 1949, had over 52,000 grass roots branches
nationwide in 1995. 
