<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Inspects Flood-Ravaged Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUNAN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today urged continued vigilance along the Yangtze River and
pledged that the government will provide for the daily needs of
flood victims.
</P>
<P>
The president arrived in Hunan Province this morning to begin a
fact-finding tour of flood-ravaged areas. Local officials briefed
the president on flood control operations and Jiang said that
receding flood waters along the Yangtze do not indicate the end of
this year's flood season. He noted that water levels in many
sections remain above danger levels.
</P>
<P>
He called for continued vigilance and urged people engaged in
the flood control effort to take effective measures to ensure the
safety of levees and strive for ultimate success.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also General Secretary of the Chinese Communist
Party Central Committee and Chairman of the Central Military
Commission, said efforts must be made to guarantee the basic daily
needs of people in flood-stricken areas.
</P>
<P>
"We must ensure victims have adequate food, clean drinking
water and clothing. They must have adequate shelter and access to
immediate medical care," Jiang told local officials, adding that
local governments should make arrangements to help victims cope
with the coming winter.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to the great importance in stablizing social order
and maintaining security in disaster areas. He said efforts must
be made to ensure that schools open on schedule and noted that
universities should provide assistance and provide financial aid
to students from disaster areas if necessary.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also discussed reconstruction and stressed that special
attention should be attached to reducing burdens on
farmers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
