<DOCNO> XIE19980903.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China-Japan Non-Governmental Personages Meeting Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The seventh Sino-Japanese
Non-Governmental Personages Council meeting concluded here
Thursday after adopting a resolution calling on the two countries
to expand cooperation and coordination in various fields.
</P>
<P>
While looking into the economic development in East Asia in the
21st century, China and Japan should seek cooperation and
coordination in such fields as regional economy, finance and
currencies, the resolution said.
</P>
<P>
During the four-day meeting, which was held to mark the 20th
anniversary of the signing of Sino-Japanese Peace and Friendship
Treaty, some 60 celebrities from the two countries exchanged views
on world situation, Sino-Japanese ties, Asian financial turmoil
and Sino-Japanese scientific and technological exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Chinese Committee described the Sino-Japanese
ties as generally good, noting that remarkable achievements have
been made in political, economic, technological and cultural
spheres.
</P>
<P>
However, they also pointed out that some problems such as
recognization of history and the Taiwan issue, which could affect
the smooth development of bilateral relations, are still existing.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Committee members also urged the Japanese
government to make clear that Taiwan would not be included into
the scope of the new guidelines on Japan-U.S. defense cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They said that celebrities of the two countries should continue
to play their active role in promoting governmental exchanges
between the two countries and make contributions to the
establishment of good-neighboring cooperative ties toward the next
century.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Japanese Committee said that Japan-China
economic exchange has entered a new development phase, adding that
the two countries should expand cooperation in fields like
investment and technology transfers.
</P>
<P>
As two important countries in Asian and world economy, Japan
and China should take lessons from the current Asian financial
crisis and set up governmental and non-governmental economic
consultative bodies as soon as possible, they noted.
</P>
<P>
The celebrities also decided that the next meeting would be
held in Beijing two years later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
