<HEADLINE> Senior CPC Official Meets With Malian Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Hu Jintao, member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, met here today with a delegation
led by Ibrahima N'Diaye, general secretary of the African Party of
Solidarity and Justice of Mali (APSJM).
</P>
<P>
Hu voiced his thanks for Mali's adherence to the "one China"
position and its support of China's peaceful reunification effort.
</P>
<P>
China and Mali enjoy a traditional friendship and the two have
always supported each other with fruitful cooperation in every
area despite dramatic changes in the international situation.
</P>
<P>
The frank and in-depth exchange between the CPC and the APSJM
have increased mutual understanding and given new impetus to the
growth of friendly ties between the two countries, Hu said.
</P>
<P>
The CPC will make unremitted efforts together with the APSJM to
advance relations between the two parties and the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also Chinese vice-president, briefed the visitors on
China's current flood-control campaign.
</P>
<P>
