<HEADLINE> Tianjin-New Siberia Air Route Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A new regular international
air route connecting Tianjin and New Siberia was opened this
morning with the landing at Tianjin Airport of a plane from New
Siberia, Russia.
</P>
<P>
The route will operate every Monday and Thursday, with a flight
distance of 3,000 kilometers, and flying time of 4 hours.
</P>
<P>
This is the fourth air route from Tianjin Airport to countries
of the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS).
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Airport now has 7 regular international air routes
to 8 cities in countries including the Republic of Korea, Japan
and Russia. 
