<HEADLINE> Mandela to Visit Mauritius </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela will pay a two-day state visit to Mauritius next
week during which the two countries will sign several bilateral
accords on cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The visit, scheduled between September 10 and 12, will
"further strengthen and enhance the already excellent relations"
between the two countries, South African Foreign Ministry said in
a statement Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Mandela and Mauritian Prime Minister Navin
Ramgoolam, who paid a state visit to South Africa in February,
will sign several bilateral agreements on sport, arts and
culture, and on cooperation in science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Mandela is scheduled to address the National Assembly of the
Mauritian parliament in Port Louis, the capital, on September 12,
and will witness the signing of two private sector business
agreements between the two countries before winding up his visit
that day.
</P>
<P>
After the visit, Mandela will attend a summit of the Southern
African Development Community (SADC) in Mauritius, scheduled for
September 13 and 14. 
</P>
</TEXT>
