<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swissair Suffers Eight Fatal Crashes Since 1955 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Swissair has encountered eight
fatal crashes since 1955 including one on Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
-- June 19, 1955: a CV-240 crashed because of lack of fuel at
Folkestone of Britain, killing three people.
</P>
<P>
-- July 15, 1956: a CV-440 crashed at Shannon of Ireland with
four deaths.
</P>
<P>
-- June 18, 1957: a DC-3 crashed into the lake of Constance in
a training flight with nine deaths.
</P>
<P>
-- September 4, 1963: a Caravelle on fire crashed at
Durrenasch, Switzerland with 80 deaths
</P>
<P>
-- February 10, 1967: a CV-440 crashed in a training flight
near Zurich with four deaths.
</P>
<P>
-- February 21, 1970: a CV-990 crashed at Wurenlingen,
Switzerland after a bomb explosion with 47 deaths.
</P>
<P>
-- October 7, 1979: a DC-8 went out of the runway of the Athens
airport with 14 deaths. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
