<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EDS: Updates with Speech at News Conference hke090344 --Sacked Anwar Ibrahim Says There is Conspiracy Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Anwar Ibrahim, who was
sacked Wednesday as Malaysia's Deputy Prime Minister and Finance
Minister, said Thursday that there is a conspiracy at the highest
level to ruin him.
</P>
<P>
He told a news conference at his own house here that he was
given a choice by the prime minister to resign or to be removed.
</P>
<P>
"I was not prepared to resign as I was already aware of a pact
or conspiracy at the highest level to ruin me," said Anwar.
</P>
<P>
This is because there was no reasonable truth or basis in
allegations against him to justify his removal, Anwar said.
</P>
<P>
He said that he is still the deputy president of the ruling
United Malays National Organization (UMNO) as he was elected to
the post.
</P>
<P>
The UMNO Supreme Council is scheduled to meet Thursday night.
Anwar said, "I will use tonight's forum to defend myself."
</P>
<P>
Anwar also disclosed that he had undergone two DNA tests,
including an independent test outside the country, which proved
that an allegation that he was the father of an illegitimate child
was false.
</P>
<P>
"What I speak (of) is justice. It is tragic that government
institutions have been used by people who plotted against me to
frame up and fabricate charges. If I, as the number two man in the
country (until yesterday), cannot get justice and have become a
victim of these allegations, then I am sorry for this country," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Confirming he was given an ultimatum by the prime minister
Wednesday whether to reign or to be removed, Anwar said that he
was not prepared to resign and had repeatedly told the prime
minister that there was a conspiracy at the highest level to
topple him.
</P>
<P>
It included certain cabinet ministers, UMNO Supreme Council
members, corporate figures, people of substantial means and
outsiders, Anwar said.
</P>
<P>
He however said that this action against him did not originate
from UMNO as a political party.
</P>
<P>
He said that he had already expected to be arrested to face
charges under the Official Secret Act (OSA) and possibly the
Internal Security Act (ISA) or other laws.
</P>
<P>
Anwar, however, said that he would defend himself and his
family members and had initiated the legal process.
</P>
<P>
Four affidavits were filed Thursday morning by Attorney-General
Mohtar Abdullah, Prisons Department Director-General Omar Mohamed
Dan and two senior police officers at the High Court here in
response to the application of Magnum public affairs director S.
Nallakaruppan who is the author of the book "50 Dalil Mengapa
Anwar Tidak Boleh Jadi PM" (50 Reasons Why Anwar Cannot Become PM)
which contained allegations of sexual misconduct against Anwar
Ibrahim.
</P>
<P>
The affidavits contain various allegations against Anwar,
including sexual misconduct and posing a threat to national
security.
</P>
<P>
Anwar was alleged to have very close relations with
Nallakaruppan who is now being held under the Internal Security
Act and is facing charges under the ISA for unlawful possession of
125 live bullets which were recovered from his Bukit Tunku home in
the course of investigations.
</P>
<P>
Manjeet Singh, one of the lawyers for Nallakaruppan, told
reporters after meeting Anwar earlier Thursday that he required
time to study four affidavits.
</P>
<P>
Anwar told reporters earlier Thursday when was leaving the
Deputy Prime Minister's official residence for his own house that
all charges against him are totally fabricated.
</P>
<P>
"It's total fabrication. I'm going to fight it all the way,"
Anwar told reporters from his vehicle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
