<HEADLINE> Australian Stocks Inch Lower After Mixed Day in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Australian share market
inched lower Thursday as investors cautiously sought out oversold
stocks that had suffered in the recent global market volatility.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index ended 2.7 points lower at
2513.3, losing early gains as Asian markets mostly headed lower.
</P>
<P>
"The uncertainty about the status of the markets and concern
about the performance of Wall Street tonight after last night's
fall (drove the market)," Morgans broker Simon Reed said.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index tumbled 17.7 points to 4442.6 while
the all resources index rose 1.24 percent, or 11.7 points, to
952.1.
</P>
<P>
"The big resources had a good day with some strength in the
metal prices combined with the lower Australian dollar and the
largely oversold position of the stocks," Reed said.
</P>
<P>
Shares in the big diversified miners jumped Thursday after
being savaged by a jittery market earlier in the week.
</P>
<P>
Resources giant BHP shares were cautiously sought by investors
after being sold off earlier in the week.
</P>
<P>
They ended 45.2 cents higher at 12.75 Australian dollars while
global miner Rio Tinto climbed 44.2 cents to 17.742 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The banking sector took a hit after ANZ bank announced that the
loss from its emerging markets debt securities would be higher
than the 78 million Australian dollars (45 million U.S. dollars)
announced in July.
</P>
<P>
The banking index slid 94.0 points to 5487.0 with ANZ bank
shedding 27 cents to 8.52 Australian dollars, National Australia
Bank dipped 56 cents to 21.50 Australian dollars, Westpac bank
slipped 19.8 cents to 9.24 Australian dollars and the Commonwealth
Bank of Australia dropped eight cents to 19.25 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the gold sector, the index jumped 2.7 points to 881.5 as he
gold price fell 1.40 U.S. dollars to 278.60 U.S. dollars per ounce
in Sydney trading.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 275.59 million shares worth 605.19
million U.S. dollars with rises outnumbering falls by 472 to 458.
</P>
</TEXT>
