<HEADLINE> Conflicts Should Be Resolved Through Consultation: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- China considers that disputes
and conflicts among nations should be resolved through
consultations in line with the UN Charter and relevant
international laws rather than by the wanton use of force, said
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao here today during a regular
press conference.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remark in response to a question on Sudan's
condemnation of the recent U.S. air raid, which claimed to target
terrorists without any concrete evidence.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government opposes any form of terrorism, Zhu said,
calling on the international community to actively study, and work
hard to eradicate the source of terrorism, and strengthen
cooperation in regard to anti-terrorism, he said.
</P>
<P>
As a permanent member of the U.N. Security Council, China will
make joint efforts with the international community to contribute
to world peace and stability, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
