<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed broadly higher Thursday on
improved trading, mainly due to follow-through buying support by
local institutional funds.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was pushed
up 6.27 percent or 18.48 points to 313.07, the all-share Emas
Index rose 4.99 points to 82.82, the Industrial Index improved
41.02 points to 613.86 points and the Second Board Index increased
by 2.95 points to 79.69
</P>
<P>
Gainers outnumbered losers 610 to 67 while 67 counters were
unchanged, 67 untraded and 40 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover surged to 310.413 million shares valued at
377.453 million ringgit (about 99.329 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 183.379 million shares worth 334.877 million ringgit
(about 88.125 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Main Board turnover rose to 299.397 million shares valued
at 366.594 million ringgit (about 96.472 million U.S. dollars)
from 178.163 million shares worth 330.018 million ringgit (about
86.846 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Second Board turnover enlarged to 11.016 million shares
valued at 10.859 million ringgit (about 2.857 million U.S.
dollars) from 5.216 million shares valued at 4.859 million ringgit
(about 1.278 million U.S. dollars) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover also firmed to 5.980 million shares valued
at 7.639 million ringgit (about 2.01 million U.S. dollars) from
Wednesday's 4.087 million shares valued at 9.274 million ringgit
(about 2.44 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 10.258
million shares traded on the Main Board, industrial products
23.615 million shares, construction 43.326 million shares,
trade/services 113.353 million shares, infrastructures 1.278
million shares, finance 58.144 million shares, hotels 444,000
shares, properties 21.932 million shares, plantation 5.174 million
shares, mining 625,200 shares, trusts 184,000 shares, closed/fund
54,000 shares and loans 21.009 million shares. 
</P>
