<HEADLINE> China, Israel to Further Cooperation on Higher Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- China and Israel today agreed
to strengthen their cooperation on higher education.
</P>
<P>
The China Scholarship Council and Israel's Bar-Ilan University
signed here today a memo of understanding on dispatching 100
Chinese post-doctors to Bar-Ilan University for further study,
starting from next month.
</P>
<P>
These post-doctors will study physics, biochemistry,
mathematics, social sciences and Jewish studies at Bar-Ilan
University in the coming years, thanks to a fellowship program
sponsored by Fred Kort, a Jewish American.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Israeli Post-Doctoral Fellowship Program is expected
to facilitate academic and scientific ties between the two
countries. It is also the largest academic exchanges between
Israel and China.
</P>
<P>
Established in 1955, Bar-Ilan University has grown to become
Israel's second largest university. Its faculties include natural
and social sciences, humanities, Jewish studies and law.
</P>
<P>
Wei Yu, Chinese vice-minister of education and director of the
China Scholarship, expressed the hope in the signing ceremony that
the results of the program will contribute to the growth of
Sino-Israeli friendship.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Ambassador to China Ora Namir said that the two
countries will strengthen their ties "based on mutual work on
education cooperation."  
</P>
</TEXT>
