<HEADLINE> 27 Tamil Rebels Killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Wednesday killed at least 27 Tamil rebels in separate places in
north and east of the country, according to military spokesman
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops operating ahead of
defenses sniped and killed three rebels in west of Olumadu in the
north of the country on Wednesday morning.
</P>
<P>
Around 8:30 a.m. Wednesday in Kilinochchi in the Northern
Province, government troops backed by armor and artillery launched
a limited operation in places west and east of kilinochchi town to
locate and destroyed rebel bunker lines, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
About 10 rebels were killed and another 10 or more wounded
during the operation in the southern flank.
</P>
<P>
In the eastern flank, Dewage said six rebel bunkers were
completely destroyed, and according to ground troops' reports, at
least 10 terrorists were killed and a large number of others
injured during the operation.
</P>
<P>
On the same day afternoon in east of Mankulam, government
troops observed a rebel bunker line and destroyed it with
artillery fire, said Dewage, adding that at least four rebels were
killed and 10 others injured.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
