<HEADLINE> Strong Earthquake Hits Northeastern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 3 (Xinhua) --- A strong earthquake measuring 6.0
on the open-ended Richter scale jolted Iwate Prefecture in
northeastern Japan on Thursday afternoon, the Meteorological Agency
said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage or casualties and no
tsunami or tidal wave warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which occurred at 4:58 p.m. (local time), was also felt
in neighboring Akita Prefecture.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the tremor was not far below the surface in the
northern part of Iwate Prefecture, the agency said. 
