<HEADLINE> Myanmar, S. Korea to Jointly Produce Iron Sheet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yangon, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A Myanmar military-run company
and a South Korean firm will jointly produce CI galvanized iron
sheet in an industrial zone in the capital of Yangon, the official
newspaper New Light of Myanmar reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The iron sheet factory project, being jointly implemented by
the Union of Myanmar Economic Holdings Ltd. (UMEHL) and the
Pohang Iron and Steel Co. Ltd. of South Korea under the name of
Myanmar Posco Steel Co. Ltd., is located at the Pyinmabin
Industrial Zone in the Mingaladon Township, about 20 kilometers
north of Yangon.
</P>
<P>
This is another joint-venture factory of its kind which the
UMEHL is constructing in the industrial zone after the one with
the Myanmar One Co. Ltd. of Thailand.
</P>
<P>
In February this year, the UMEHL also reached an agreement with
 the Berger International Limited of Singapore to set up a joint-
venture factory to produce famous brand Berger paints in the zone.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar-foreign joint-venture galvanized iron sheet factories
are also being established in the Hlaingtharya, another industrial
zone in the northwest of Yangon.
</P>
<P>
There are altogether 17 industrial zones in Myanmar, including
five in Yangon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
