<HEADLINE> China Concerned with Instability in Middle East: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- China is seriously concerned
over the instability in the Middle East caused by the deadlock in
the peace talks between Arab countries and Israel, and hopes the
issue can be resolved smoothly, Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu
Bangzao said here today.
</P>
<P>
It is the call of the time and in the long-term interest of
people in the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged relevant parties to implement the United Nations
resolutions on the issue as well as agreements and commitments
already reached by the parties concerned in a bid to advance the
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Only in this way can the countries in the region enjoy genuine
security and stability, the spokesman noted. 
