<HEADLINE> 8 Cases of Cholera Reported in Northern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran has found eight cases of
cholera in the northern province of Gilan, the morning paper Iran
Daily reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Deputy director for health affairs of Gilan Medical University
Esmail Noursalehi said that four patients have been transferred to
Tehran for treatment while two are under medical care in Rasht,
and the other two in Langeroud.
</P>
<P>
Noursalehi said that some pamphlets have been published to
increase public awareness in order to prevent the disease from
spreading.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Gilan health department issued a statement on
Wednesday calling on the public to use safe drinking water, avoid
locally-produced vegetables and observe individual
hygiene. 
</P>
</TEXT>
