<HEADLINE> Switzerland Confirms Air Crash off Eastern Canadian Coast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A Swissair jet with 229 people
on board crashed in the Atlantic ocean off eastern Canada at about
0:30 GMT Thursday, according to Swiss Radio International.
</P>
<P>
Swissair Flight 111 of the wide-bodied MD-11 was on its way
from New York to Geneva when it disappeared from radar screens and
crashed about 10 kilometers off the Canadian coast of Nova Scotia.
</P>
<P>
Rescue workers say they cannot confirm reports that survivors
have been found.
</P>
<P>
Swissair says the aircraft was carrying 215 passengers and a
crew of 14. It is not yet known what caused the crash.
</P>
<P>
Reports say that the plane was attempting to make an emergency
landing at Halifax when it went missing. The pilot reported smoke
in the cockpit shortly before losing contact with air controllers.
</P>
<P>
Swissair has set up hot lines for relatives of those on
board. In Zurich, the number is 41-1-803 1717, and in Geneva it's
41-22-717 8300. There's also a number in New York, 001-800-801
0088. 
</P>
</TEXT>
