<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Experts Sent to Control Diseases in Flooded Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Sixteen experts from the Chinese
Academy of Preventive Medicine have been sent to help prevent and
control diseases in the flood-stricken areas, according to the
Ministry of Health.
</P>
<P>
The medical personnel, specialists in epidemic-disease
prevention and food and environmental hygiene, are on their way to
Hubei, Hunan, Jiangxi, Anhui, Heilongjiang, and Jilin provinces
and the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Illnesses such as colds, pink eye and dermatitis are
under control in the flooded areas, but the potential danger of
outbreaks of epidemic diseases still exists, said a health
official.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of August, the incidence of disease in the
flooded areas has been on the rise, and the Ministry of Health
recently issued an emergency circular requiring close supervision
and prompt reporting of the health situation.
</P>
<P>
Experts sent to the flooded areas will cooperate with local
doctors in investigating into the situation and directing doctors to
deal with the difficulties of disease prevention.
</P>
<P>
They are also expected to train more grassroots personnel in
disease prevention and help local governments plan disease
prevention and control, said the official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
