<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT, September 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SIEM REAP, CAMBODIA -- Cambodian Second Prime Minister Hun Sen,
accompanied by a senior Cambodian People's Party (CPP) delegation,
had an audience with King Norodom Sihanouk Thursday in Siem Reap
to discuss ways to avoid a constitutional crisis.
</P>
<P>
The CPP won the most seats in the July 26 National Assembly
election, according to the final official results announced by the
National Election Committee (NEC) on Tuesday. But the party failed
to win two-thirds of the Assembly seats needed to form a new
government by itself. Hun Sen is hoping for a revision of the
Constitution to allow his CPP to form a government with a simple
majority. (Cambodia-CPP-Audience)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- A nationwide general strike organized by Israel
Histadrut (National Trade Union) began Thursday morning
in Israel, hitting all public sectors of the country.
</P>
<P>
The strike was caused by the unsettled wage conflict between
the Histadrut and the government. The Histadrut is asking for an 8
percent wage increase for public sector workers, but the Finance
Ministry only agreed to a 0.75 percent wage increase, which the
ministry said is in addition to the recent cost of living increase
of 0.5 percent and other salary increases, such as seniority
increments. (Israel-General Strike)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Thursday called on the Afghan Taliban militia
to release all Iranian hostages as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi made the call
after the Taliban announced readiness to release three hostages,
the official news agency IRNA reported. He said that Iran calls
for release of all Iranian hostages, including diplomats, truck
driver, aid workers and IRNA reporter. (Iran-Taliban-Hostages)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
OTTAWA -- A SwissAir jet carrying 229 passengers and crew
members crashed off the coast of Nova Scotia, Canada, Wednesday
night, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The MD 11 jet, en route from New York to Geneva, declared an
emergency at 10:30 p.m. local time and attempted an emergency
landing at Halifax airport. But it disappeared moments later.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of ambulances and fire trucks were gathered along the
Canadian coastline. A Hercules aircraft and four military
helicopters were leading the search. (Canada-Plane-Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Fifteen armed ethnic Albanians died in the latest
clash with Serbian police in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The official Yugoslav news agency, Tanjug, reported on
Wednesday that a group of armed ethnic Albanians opened fire on
the Serbian police Tuesday morning in the southern town of Prizren
in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Police launched a counter-attack, killing 15 and capturing
another 15. Violence reportedly erupted again between the two
sides on Wednesday morning but no casualties were reported.
(Kosovo-Armed Conflict) 
</P>
</TEXT>
