<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Former U.S. Secretaries of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councillor and
Defense Minister Chi Haotian met here today with a U.S.-China
Society delegation led by Dr. Henry Kissinger and Cyrus Vance,
both former U.S. secretaries of state.
</P>
<P>
Chi, who also serves as vice-chairman of China's Central
Military Commission, said he is pleased to meet again with old
friends, and praised the efforts that Kissinger and Vance have
made in promoting Sino-U.S. relations.
</P>
<P>
He noted that both sides are working hard for a constructive
Sino-U.S. strategic partnership geared to the 21st century, which
is in line with the common aspirations of the peoples of both
nations.
</P>
<P>
The current relations between China and the U.S. have been hard
earned, Chi said, citing the Chinese proverb "when drinking
water, think of its source."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese people will never forget those
U.S. friends who contributed to promoting Sino-U.S. friendship and
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Chi also briefed the visitors on the Chinese military and mass
efforts in fighting the devastating floods this summer.
</P>
<P>
Kissinger joyfully recalled his first visit to China in 1971
and those who have made great efforts to open the gate for
bilateral relations, saying he is glad to see increased exchanges
and cooperation between the two countries and their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Vance said he feels happy to have such a chance to visit China
again, during which he is seeing China's changes with his own eyes.
</P>
