<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's business community
wants the sanctions imposed on Burundi by the regional
governments to be lifted, the Daily Nation newspaper reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We denounce economic sanctions because they make us less
k+WW-]Z;e against our competitor from non-sanction implementing
areas," Chairman of the Kenya National Chamber of Commerce and
Industry Kassim Owango was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
