of development while providing unfair and undue advantage to
other players in the market place.
</P>
<P>
He said they become a draw back to economic growth of the
Great Lakes region at a time when it is facing economic problems.
</P>
<P>
"It is all the more painful when the sanctions are imposed by
our leaders who are at the same time urging us to invest in the
region," he said.
</P>
<P>
Kirubi said the sanctions on Burundi only benefited the West.
</P>
<P>
"We must declare the sanctions illegal; they have not served
any purpose," said the KAM boss.
</P>
<P>
Burundi's neighbors imposed sanctions against the small
central African country in August, 1996, just a few days after
Major Pierre Buyoya seized power in Bujumbura. 
