<HEADLINE> 84,000 New Phone Lines Installed in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Over 84,000 telephone
lines which have been newly installed in Addis Ababa and other
towns during the 1997/98 fiscal year have gone operational, the
Ethiopian Herald reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's 1997/98 fiscal year ended on July 7, 1998.
</P>
<P>
The official newspapers quoted General Manager of the Public
Relations Department of the Ethiopian Telecommunications
Corporation Berhe Seyoum as saying that 70,000 telephone lines
have been installed in the western district of the capital city.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Berhe said, over 14,000 new lines have been installed
in Arada, Dessie, Kombolcha, Woldia, Jijiga and Hosana towns.
</P>
<P>
Berhe said preparations are finalized to install 10,250 new
telephone lines this year in various regions.
</P>
<P>
The general manager described the installation of over 84,000
new lines in a single year as ''a dramatic move in a country''.
</P>
<P>
There are only 160,000 telephone lines in Ethiopia and the
corporation has plans to expand its telephone services to 850,000
in the coming two or three years. 
</P>
