<HEADLINE> Iran Calls for Release of All Iranian Hostages in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Thursday called on the
Afghan Taliban militia to release all Iranian hostages as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi made the call
after the Taliban announced readiness to release three hostages,
the official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran calls for release of all Iranian hostages,
including diplomats, truck driver, aid workers and IRNA reporter.
</P>
<P>
Iran said that the Taliban forces kidnaped 11 Iranian
diplomats, an IRNA reporter, 35 truck drivers and a group of aid
workers in northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban has so far officially rejected the captivity of the
Iranian diplomats and reporter but admitted the arrest of other
Iranians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
