<HEADLINE> U.S. High School Player Declared Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 2 (Xinhua) A high school football player
who collapsed during practice was declared dead Wednesday
afternoon, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
San Bernardino County coroner's deputy Jim Sedgwick said that
Chino high school linebacker Scott Maughan took a head-to-head
hit Tuesday during tackling drills, and he died on Wednesday
afternoon. His body was kept on ventilation machines at a
hospital to give the organs a continuous orygen supply.
</P>
<P>
"Scott walked back past his caoch. His coach noticed that he
was a little unsteady," said school principal Robert Nero.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old player collapsed and was taken unconscious to
a medical center nearby.
</P>
<P>
Chino Valley Unified School District spokesman John Lynde said
the doctors underwent an hour long surgery that began about four
hours after the injury. 
</P>
</TEXT>
