<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT September 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK -- A late selling spree today cut short the Dow
industrial's strive to extend Tuesday's rebound from August's
scary selloff.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average, down 512.61 on Monday and up
288.23 Tuesday, fell 45.06 points to close at 7,782.37. The
average of 30 blue chips had been holding onto gains until the
final minutes of trading. (New York, Stocks Down)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian lower house of parliament said Wednesday
that the economic crisis is threatening the country's security.
</P>
<P>
In a statement passed unanimously, the State Duma said the
situation "poses a serious threat to the security of the Russian
Federation as a sovereign state and requires a change in the
economic policy."  (Russia-Duma-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- Thai consumer prices rose 7.6 percent year-on-year
in August, while wholesale prices jumped 12.9 percent in a
significant moderation of the country's inflation rate.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Commerce Ministry said in a statement available here
Wednesday that the Consumer Price Index (CPI) rose to 129.4, up
0.4 percent from July. In July the index was up 10 percent
year-on-year, while the wholesale price index shot up 19.5
percent. (Thailand-Inflation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korea Wednesday announced a package of monetary
and fiscal measures to revitalize its rapidly cooling domestic
demand.
</P>
<P>
Those measures aim to keep the economy from slipping into
deeper recession, said Minister of Finance and Economy Lee Kyu-sung
</P>
<P>
The package includes taking a flexible approach toward money
supply, expanding credit guarantees for small- and medium-sized
enterprises, exporters and housing builders and increasing
consumer financing instruments for buyers of houses and other
durable goods. (SKorea-Economy-Measures)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The Indonesian government has established a crisis
center in the fields of people's welfare and poverty eradication,
an assistant to Coordinating Minister for People's Welfare
Sudjono told Antara News Agency Wednesday. (Indonesia-Welfare)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PYONGYANG -- Hit severely by an unexpected abnormal weather,
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) this year is
facing a gloomy prospect in its agricultural sector and needs more
international aid, DPRK officials said Wednesday. (DPRK-Food-Aid)
</P>
</TEXT>
