<DOCNO> XIE19980903.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Expresses Concern Over Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria is deeply concerned
over the deteriorating situations in Kosovo, said Bulgarian
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Radko Vlaikov Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Kosovo conflict retains its explosive potential despite the
extraordinary concerted efforts of the international community and
the countries in the region,Vlaikov said.
</P>
<P>
The current situation in Kosovo is intolerable and must be
changed, he said.
</P>
<P>
To end this and bring success to the negotiating table, Vlaikov
said the cessation of hostilities between the two warring parties
is a necessary condition.
</P>
<P>
He also noted the identification of the representatives of the
Kosovo Albanians, whether they will be legitimate in the talk, is
an important factor towards the success of the negotiation.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said, a form of broad autonomy should be sought
which would provide lasting satisfaction to the demands of both
warring parties.
</P>
<P>
``I believe nothing has changed in the stand of Bulgaria and
other countries in the region, in that we categorically oppose any
revision of boundaries in the region," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Vlaikov called on the international community to coordinate on
their decisions concerning matters in Kosovo. The unity of action
with the Contact Group should be guaranteed and the stands of the
countries in the region should be considered, he said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman criticized that the economic sanctions imposed on
Bosnia and Herzegovina were counterproductive and would affect
adversely other third countries, like Bulgaria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
