<HEADLINE> China's Prices to Be Kept Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- China's prices will still be
kept at a low level in the second half of this year, though the
inflation rate is expected to turn to a positive one in the
period, predicted Qiu Xiaohua, spokesman for the State Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
"With the overall economic climate turning better, the
situation of a negative inflation rate will end in the second half
of this year," he said at a news conference today.
</P>
<P>
Because of the fact of a "buyer's market" and the impact of the
Asian fianancial crisis, China witnessed sluggish market this
year and China's inflation rate has been dropping for several
months, Qiu noted.
</P>
<P>
In July this year, the consumer price index dropped by 1.4
percent over the same period last year and the retail price index
dropped by 3.2 percent. 
</P>
