<HEADLINE> Ten Presidents Confirm Participation in Rio Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA City, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Ten presidents of Latin
America are to attend the 12th Rio Group summit beginning on
Friday, the organization commission announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ivette Franco Koroneos, chairman of the commission said the
presidents of Bolivia, Chile, Colombia, Ecuador, Guyana, Mexico,
Panama, Peru, Paraguay and Venezuela will come to the regional
event.
</P>
<P>
Brazil will send its vice president, and Argentina and Uruguay
will send their prime ministers to the summit, Franco Koroneos
added.
</P>
<P>
El Salvador had still not confirmed, he said.
</P>
