Gaviria, President of the Interamerican Developing Bank Enrique
Iglesias and the Central American Parliament President Jorge
Singer will also be present at the event.
</P>
<P>
Peace, security, democracy and relations between Latin America
and the Caribbean and Europe will be the main topics on the agenda.
</P>
<P>
The presidents will also discuss the free trade zone in the
Americas, the introduction of the new currency in Europe and the
Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
As host country, Panama will promote the topics of education
and unemployment in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Rio Group is formed by Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil,
Colombia, Chile, Mexico, Paraguay, Uruguay, Ecuador, Peru, Panama,
Venezuela, Guyana representing the Caribbean, and El Salvador
representing Central America. 
