<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan police avert Another Telecom Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 3 (Xinhua) -- An attempt to blast another
electrical transformer in the deep south of the country was
averted by Sri Lankan police Wednesday, according to police here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said an alert policeman of a nearby building helped
to detect a bomb placed under an electrical transformer at
Hikkaduwa town, thus helping to avert a major disaster Wednesday
morning.
</P>
<P>
The policeman had seen two persons placing a parcel under the
transformer and then fleeing from the site.
</P>
<P>
He had immediately informed the police who rushed to scene and
found a bomb weighing 250 grams. The police removed the bomb from
the transformer and kept it on the road. The Bomb Disposal Unit
arrived and defused it, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The bomb had been timed to explode later during the day when
the area would have been crowded, said the sources, adding that
police are conducting further investigations in the area to arrest
the fled two suspects.
</P>
<P>
At least 15 telecom buildings or electrical transformers have
been exploded during the May and June this year by the Tamil
rebels who are fighting for a separate Tamil state in the country.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
