<HEADLINE> Shanghai Issues Licenses to Qualified Mineral Water Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
economic and financial center, recently introduced a licensing
system to bring local mineral water producers and the production
and marketing of low quality water products under government
control.
</P>
<P>
Some 106 local firms producing mineral water, purified water
and various other types of refined water products have received
certification.
</P>
<P>
Local officials report the city is home to over 200 bottled
water plants, including a number of plants which failed to fulfill
standards for quality and equipment.
</P>
<P>
Official surveys over the past three years have shown that only
50 percent of local water products meet national standards.
</P>
<P>
Over 20 percent of the plants have closed since implementation
of the new policy, according to local officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
