<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Province Curbs Corruption Involving Government Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- The Government of east China's
Jiangsu Province is determined to conduct official purchases
through public bidding in order to curb corruption related to
malpractices in government-funded projects.
</P>
<P>
Provincial authorities recently issued a set of regulations
instructing government bodies at or above the county level to
adopt the new method for purchases.
</P>
<P>
Local governments have since introduced public bidding for a
large number of purchase items, including an 800-million-yuan
construction project in Taizhou, one of the largest projects in
the nation to adopt the new purchase.
</P>
<P>
Malpractices such as bribery and embezzlement have been rampant
in terms of government in recent years, and a large number of
government officials have been convicted of accepting bribes.
</P>
