<HEADLINE> New Flight Open to Connect Taiwan and Ningbo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A chartered flight connecting
Taiwan, Macao and Ningbo in East China will open this month,
today's China Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ningbo City Government, the first flight
from the city is set for September 22.
</P>
<P>
The flight will first make a stopover in Macao before leaving
for Taiwan, There will be two flights every week, according to
the plan.
</P>
<P>
The opening of the charter signals a partially direct air route
to Taiwan, authorities said. The flight carrier was not announced
by the authorities.
</P>
<P>
A Taiwan resident will be able to visit the port city in
Zhejiang Province without changing planes in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there are no direct flights connecting Taiwan and
the mainland. Due to restrictions, visitors from Taiwan must
go through Hong Kong or Macao to take flights to the mainland.
</P>
