<HEADLINE> China to Construct Beijing-Zhangjiakou Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 3 (Xinhua) -- China will build an
expressway from Beijing to Zhangjiakou, a city in the east end of
the Great Wall in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
As an extension of the Dandong-Lhasa national highway, the
Beijing-Zhangjiakou expressway will be the main passage for
expanding economic and cultural exchanges among regions in west
China.
</P>
<P>
The construction, estimated at 3 billion yuan, is expected to
be completed within three years.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion, the travel time by bus between Beijing and
Zhangjiakou will be shortened from the current four hours to two.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-Zhangjiakou expressway will be helpful for the sale
of farm and side-line produces from Zhangjiakou, transporting coal
from Datong in north China's Shanxi Province, and stimulating the
economy of poverty-stricken areas along the expressway.  
</P>
</TEXT>
