<HEADLINE> CD-Rom on Xinjiang Autonomous Region Goes on Sale </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 3 (Xinhua) -- A CD-ROM on various aspects of
the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region in northwest China produced
by the Xinjiang People's Publishing House went on sale Wednesday
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The 300,000-character CD-ROM contains more than 1,000 photos,
30 charts, film material and folk songs of the region.
</P>
<P>
Compiled by the autonomous region's development planning
commission and publicity department, the CD-ROM offers a vivid
description of the autonomous region's scenic sites, economic
achievements, and industrial and commercial information.
</P>
</TEXT>
