<HEADLINE>   15 Killed in Kosovo Clash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen armed ethnic
Albanians died in the latest clash with Serbian police in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The official Yugoslav news agency, Tanjug, reported on
Wednesday that a group of armed ethnic Albanians opened fire on
the Serbian police Tuesday morning in the southern town of Prizren
in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Police launched a counter-attack, killing 15 and capturing
another 15. Violence reportedly erupted again between the two
sides on Wednesday morning but no casualties were reported.
</P>
<P>
Sources said another group of armed Albanians entered
Yugoslavia Tuesday morning. They opened fire on the Yugoslav
frontier force 500 meters inside the Yugoslav border. The
Albanians were defeated and fled back into Albania. 
</P>
