<HEADLINE> Beijing Tourism Shrinks Because of Asian Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 3 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's tourism sector has
begun to shrink due to the Asian economic crisis, with the
number of tourists visiting the Chinese capital falling by 20.46
percent between January and July.
</P>
<P>
The nosedive commenced in May and the total number of tourists
visiting Beijing fell sharply by 15 percent in July, the normal
peak season, according to officials from the city's tourism bureau.
</P>
<P>
A total of 178,000 foreign tourists visited Beijing in July.
</P>
<P>
Japan and the United States continue to be the leading two
countries in terms of tourist arrivals, with Malaysia falling
from fourth to eighth place.
</P>
<P>
The number of visitors from European countries has jumped by
over four percent, with Germany ranking first with 66,000 tourist
arrivals, followed by the United Kingdom and Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
