<HEADLINE> Samaranch, Venizelos Sign Protocol for Cultural Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 2 (Xinhua) -- Visiting President of the
International Olympic Committee (IOC) Juan Antonio Samaranch and
Greek Culture Minister Vangelos Venizelos signed Wednesday the
protocal establishing the "cultural Olympics" international
institute.
</P>
<P>
A second cooperation protocol was also signed Wednesday
between the Olympia Archaeological Museum and the Lausanne
Olympic Games Museum.
</P>
<P>
The Greek side has proposed to the United Nations
Educational,Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) the new
institute have a status as a non-governmental organization, based
at Olympia, in the southwestern Greek peninsula of Peleponnesos.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after the signing ceremony, Venizelos said that the
first cultural Olympics would be held at the 2000 Sydney Olympic
games leading to the Athens 2004 games while the four-pronged
subject would focus on the civilization of peace, social
cohesion, the society of information and the civilization of
innovation.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Samaranch stressed here that the texts they
signed was an important beginning for the 2004 games.
</P>
<P>
The IOC president said that he always supported the idea the
games had two dimensions, an atheletic and a cultural one, and
that the 2004 games in Athens would have a third one, the historic
al. 
</P>
