<HEADLINE> Senior Kenyan Official Dies in Blazed Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 2 (Xinhua) -- A top Kenyan governmental
official died Wednesday in a mysterious blaze at his Nairobi
home, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
Alexander Kiptanui Sawe, 54, as Permanent Secretary of the
Directorate of Personnel Management at the Office of the
President, was one of Kenya's top three civil servants.
</P>
<P>
His wife, Joan Jebichii, suffered serious burns all over her
body and was admitted to Nairobi Hospital.
</P>
<P>
The couple were trapped in their first floor bedroom when fire
broke out at 5:45 a.m. local time. Neighbors alerted by smoke
billowing from the windows called the police and fire brigade and
then smashed their way into the blazing home through the roof in
a desperate bid to rescue the family.
</P>
<P>
They found Mrs. Sawe clinging to the window grille in the
toilet where she had run for safety.
</P>
<P>
The dead was due to fly out of the country for a meeting on
Tuesday evening but it was rescheduled for Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Only the top floor of the home was destroyed in the blaze. The
ground floor remained intact.
</P>
<P>
The couple's only child, 18-year-old Nicholas Sawe, who
returned to Braeburn School in Nairobi on Tuesday had escaped the
disaster.
</P>
<P>
"We do not know what caused the blaze. Fire experts are
investigating," said the police.
</P>
<P>
President Daniel arap Moi issued a condolence message to
Sawe's family in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Sawe, born in 1944, was named as an under secretary in the
Office of the President in June, 1987.
</P>
<P>
In February 1990, he was transferred to the Department of
Dfense as Deputy Secretary, a post he held until January 1997
when he was appointed Permanent Secretary and Director of
Personnel Management. 
</P>
</TEXT>
